node.title: Victoria has recorded 797 new local COVID-19 cases and eight deaths
node.alt: A woman in blue PPE holds up a syringe containing Pfizer vaccine.
node.description: There are now 14,131 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 424 people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 797\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and eight\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 14,131\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 424\u00a0people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.\u00a0", "There are 394\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 72\u00a0are in intensive care and 44\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 61\u00a0people are in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections are no longer considered active.", "The new cases were identified from 53,527\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 7,191\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
